A man, John Onyema, who allegedly beat his wife, Esther to death, was on Wednesday docked in an Ebute Meta Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State. The defendant, 53, had appeared on a charge of murder. His plea was not taken. The Prosecutor, Insp. Emmanuel Silas, had urged the court to remand the defendant for 30 days at first instance, pending advice from the Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP). Silas alleged that the defendant committed the offence on Feb. 3, about 10:30 a.m., at Lady-Lak, Bariga. Girl-child: Focus on digital skills, innovation ― Pantami Bayelsa Assembly gets new speaker, deputy speaker [BREAKING] Certificate forgery: Court clears Wada as Kogi… Sanwo-Olu vows to uphold sanctity of judiciary ALSO READ: Bayelsa Assembly gets new speaker, deputy speaker He also alleged that the defendant had beaten his wife Esther, to death on the said day after an argument ensued between them. The offence, however, contravened Section 223 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, which prescribes a death sentence for convict. The Chief Magistrate, Mr O.O. Olatunji ordered the remand of the defendant at the Ikoyi Custodial Centre pending receipt of advice. Olatunji, however, adjourned the case until March 17. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.